# Project Boundaries

Product name: Dramatica-Informed Writing Assistant.

Repo path: `/home/tjrpirateking/projects/WritingAssistantApplication`.

GitHub repo: `telesjr90/writingassistant`.

This app is local-first and analysis-only. It may store, edit, save, reload, and organize owner-authored prose, notes, research, references, metadata, and materials, but AI must not generate story prose.

Never write, rewrite, continue, imitate, polish, improve, expand, or extend story prose. Never generate dialogue, chapters, scenes, story passages, replacement prose, bridge prose, or style imitation.

Use the standard refusal message exactly when refusing prose-writing requests:

```text
I can analyze structure and ask diagnostic questions, but I cannot write or rewrite story prose.
```

Owner-authored content saves must not be overblocked as AI prose generation. Scene, chapter, note, material, bible, storyform, raw idea, and owner decision fields can store owner-authored text when the owner is saving their own material.

Story Check, OMI, future extractors, NotebookLM-like outputs, retrieved references, and future Writer Assistant Core outputs remain candidate-only until owner approval. Schema validity, model confidence, extractor output, and NotebookLM aggregation do not establish story truth.

OMI is the central candidate review and promotion system. Extracted, manual, and future model-assisted story knowledge must create OMI candidates first, with evidence/provenance where practical.

Approved project truth comes only from owner-approved memory/canon records. Pending, rejected, archived, duplicate, uncertain, and needs-revision candidates are not canon. Approved candidates are not durable canon until future apply-promotion explicitly applies them into approved memory/canon.

Promotion records are audit-only until future apply-promotion exists. Runtime apply-promotion remains unimplemented unless a task explicitly implements it. Do not imply that promotion records mutate `memory/*.json`, `bible.json`, `storyform.json`, scenes, notes, materials, or project metadata.

Dramatica-specific implementation remains deferred unless a task explicitly says otherwise. General story-knowledge relationships, timeline, continuity, and plot-thread assistance must not be labeled as Dramatica proof.

Fine-tuning remains paused unless explicitly restarted. Do not create JSONL, promote dataset records, update `training/data/dataset_manifest.json`, run training, run RunPod smoke, or call Ollama/live models unless the user explicitly requests that track.

External extractor dependencies remain future-only unless explicitly approved after a dedicated spike evaluates license, maintenance, runtime cost, privacy/local-first behavior, evidence grounding, safety, candidate-only behavior, and OMI integration.
